caption: This place offers fantastic service as well as tasty food. The best restaurant in the area. The drinks and food arrived quick and the rates were reasonable. Highly recommended.

I ordered so many apps, my favs were the wings, the crab cake sliders, plantains and cocktail patties. All delicious!! Def will be back!

The customer service is constantly rapid, good mood, welcoming employees. Will visit again when I arrive in the area.

Let me start with the positive.  The space itself was very clean and decorated very nicely with things from Jamaica.  The waitstaff was friendly enough.  My husband ordered the "House special" drink and it was excellent, he enjoyed it.  Now to explain the one star.  We waited over an hour and a half for our food, I only ordered two appetizers.  He ordered curry chicken.  We were the only party in the restaurant and the server told us twice that the kitchen was "backed up".  We couldn't figure out with who as our party were the only ones there.  When the food finally arrived his plate looked a mess save for the rice and peas which was formed into a circle the chicken and cabbage seemed just kind of tossed onto the plate.  For it to be curry chicken, it really didn't have any sauce, the rice was too moist  and the entire plate was bland.  I ordered cocktail patties and plantains (I must stress I waited an hour and a half for appetizers).  To their credit they seemed house made but they barely had any meat inside and where also bland.  I really wouldn't feel right recommending this place to anyone except for maybe drinks.  Our entire party had similar critiques for the food, it was all bland and "just ok".  They definitely have alot of room for improvement.  Go at your own risk
Cozy, romantic, quaint clean restaurant with delicious food abd good service.
Food was amazing! I had the jerk salmon it was made with the perfect amount of crispiness🤤 nice vibe and delicious rum punch as well
Quaint Atmosphere. Food was tasty and filling. Drinks from the happy hour were on par with other local fair
I really love it here. I live nearby so I always hang out by Kingston. It’s super chill, great vibe, good food, great service and very friendly. Everything you need in your causal neighborhood  bar.
Great vibes, especially during live band nights. Recommend the rum punch and anything jerk. Friendly staff. An after work wine down for sure and weekend jam.

The service was excellent! We visited from DC and had the resta pasta which had a wonderful jerk spice and flavor that wasn't too overwhelming but spicy enough to eat with the fresh festival bread. The oxtails were delicious and falling off the bone. Portions were more than generous and I highly recommend when you're in the city to stop by!

Delicious food and super friendly service. We came late at night with a large party and the waitress wasn't even phased: she treated us better than other places would during the middle of the day. The fried plantains are the perfect mix of sweet and savory. The goat curry was incredible, but they were sadly out of roti by the time we arrived. I would highly recommend this place for laid back dinners.

Ordered Rasta Pasta with Jerk Salmon, Make sure you check your order before leaving because my food was not completely sealed, allot of spillige in the bag. The pasta was undercooked also, very tough to chew. The waitress and bartender was very kind.

Came here for a last minute dinner with my mom. I had been here before for my birthday and had a great time. However, this will be my last time patronizing them. My mom ordered oxtails with rice and peas. The waitress/bartender came back a few minutes later to tell us the rice and peas were hard and she should order a different side. My mom switched her order to curry shrimp with festival and cabbage because who eats oxtails with anything other than rice? Same server came back a few moments later to tell us they did not have curry shrimp. My mom finally ordered CURRY salmon. We waited 45 minutes. She was served JERK salmon. We were charged for the festival which she was forced to order. The salmon was over cooked. We were offered a free side to make up for their mistakes, however, my mom and I will not be returning. Ever.
Amazing food! Always a great atmosphere. One of the hidden gems of Harlem.
The food is delicious and makes me yearn for home in the Caribbean!

Kingston is a really nice restaurant in the midst of Harlem. In the middle of all the soul food and African restaurants, it is nice to have a Caribbean offering as well. What I like most about this establishment is the service and the music. They play classic reggae tracks that if you are a fan, you love the atmosphere. The server was also extremely nice and police and that was a big plus for me. We ordered the oxtail and the curry goat. The curry goat was very salty sadly and uneatable., and my brother had the same experience with it when he went before me so that is their main drawback. However, the oxtail was pretty good and I heard their salmon is great as well. However, a bunch of stuff on their menu was not present when we went to dine there, which was a big disappointment because we had to keep switching our order. For the music and ambiance alone, though, I would recommend this place, along with if you order the right item.

The oxtails are superb. The hostess is wonderful warm and welcoming. If you want a taste of Jamaica's best Kingston is the place. It is now our favorite Harlem restaurant.
